.TH "comedi_request_region" 9 "comedi_request_region" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
comedi_request_region \- Request an I/O region for a legacy driver
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" comedi_request_region
.BI "(struct comedi_device *dev "  ","
.BI "unsigned long start "  ","
.BI "unsigned long len "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
COMEDI device.
.IP "start" 12
Base address of the I/O region.
.IP "len" 12
Length of the I/O region.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Requests the specified I/O port region which must start at a non-zero
address.

On success, \fIdev->iobase\fP is set to the base address of the region and
\fIdev->iolen\fP is set to its length.

Returns 0 on success, -EINVAL if \fIstart\fP is 0, or -EIO if the request
fails.
